ta":{"matching_schema":"tour_matching_profiles_embedded_v2","embedded_for":"atockorea_tour_marketplace","source_of_truth_note":"matching_profile fields scored against atockorea matching algorithm v2. Single fixed route; no variant overrides.","audit_summary":"Southwest-Jeju Hydrangea Festival route — 9-hr small-group minicoach loop. 5 substantive POI anchors + 1 compound-stop pairing: 1 west-coast emerald beach (Hyeopjae) + 1 120-min hydrangea festival anchor (Hallim Park, June Hydrangea Festival, 9 themed gardens + 2 lava-tube limestone caves) + 1 compound stop (Jusangjeolli columnar + Cheonjeyeon waterfall, Natural Monuments 443 + 378) + 1 hydrangea tunnel anchor (Camellia Hill — 172,000 m², Korea''s earliest hydrangeas) + 1 tea-culture finale (Osulloc / Amorepacific). Designed for **June peak hydrangea window (June 10–25)** with Hallim caves + Camellia Hall + Osulloc museum as the 3-tier indoor weather-fallback stack. **Catalog-novel pattern**: Jusangjeolli+Cheonjeyeon compound stop is the first of its kind in the catalog. Cross-batch reuse: 3 of 5 substantive bodies imported verbatim (15a T2 Hyeopjae, 15a T1 Camellia Hill, 14a T2 Osulloc); Hallim Park authored fresh + compound stop authored fresh.","score_rationale":{"high_scores":{"southwest_jeju_fit=1.0":"All 5 substantive stops are on the southwest corridor (Hallim, Jungmun, Andeok, Seogwang)","hydrangea_festival_anchor_count=3":"Hallim June Hydrangea + Camellia Hill hydrangea tunnel + Osulloc tea-garden green tone","hydrangea_tunnel_visit=True":"Unique to this route — Camellia Hill''s signature pergola tunnel","natural_monument_anchor_count=2":"Jusangjeolli (NM 443, 2005) + Cheonjeyeon (NM 378, 1993)","two_dimensional_caves_fit=1.0":"Hallim''s Hyeopjaegul + Ssangyonggul are uniquely classified as the only lava-tube + limestone caves in the world","honeymoon_fit=1.0":"Camellia Hill is one of Korea''s top wedding-snap photo destinations + lower-impact pacing","compound_stop_count=1":"Jusangjeolli+Cheonjeyeon compound is a catalog-novel pattern"},"low_scores":{"stair_climb_demand=0.2":"No tuff-cone climb (Seongsan) — only Cheonjeyeon''s 50-step descent + Hallim''s gentle cave stairs","tuff_cone_climb_fit=0.0":"No tuff cone on this route — sister tour east route has Seongsan","winter_visitors_seeking_floral_peak":"Hydrangea peak is June; winter visitors get Camellia Hill camellia bloom but not hydrangea tunnel","private_tour_fit=0.05":"Fixed small-group itinerary preserves the operator''s cave timing + lunch pairing"}},"locale_adaptation":{"current_locale":"en","ko_localization_status":"TODO"},"related_products":{"season_pair_east_route":"jeju-hydrangea-festival-tour-east-route (existing — different POIs: Ilchul Land, Hueree Nature Park, east coast)","off_season_fallback":"jeju-west-south-full-day-authentic-tour (year-round west+south coverage)","same_season_alternative":"jeju-cherry-blossom-tour-east-route (different season — spring)","note":"Two hydrangea tours coexist with different routes (east + southwest). User preference for east vs southwest can be inferred from POI tags."},"anchor_pois":["Hyeopjae Beach","Hallim Park","Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff","Cheonjeyeon Falls","Camellia Hill","O''Sulloc Tea Museum"],"anchor_poi_keys":["hyeopjae_beach","hallim_park","daepo_jusangjeolli_cliff","cheonjeyeon_falls","camellia_hill","osulloc_tea_museum"],"competing_products":["jeju-hydrangea-festival-tour-east-route","jeju-west-south-full-day-authentic-tour","jeju-southern-top-unesco-spots-tour","southwest-hallasan-osulloc-aewol"],"primary_themes":["jeju","southwest_jeju","west_jeju","hydrangea_festival","summer_flowers","garden","botanical_garden","tea_culture","natural_monument","columnar_jointing","waterfall","lava_tube"],"secondary_themes":["hyeopjae_beach","biyangdo_island","hallim_park","hyeopjaegul_cave","ssangyonggul_cave","two_dimensional_caves","daepo_jusangjeolli","cheonjeyeon_falls","seonimgyo_bridge","seven_nymph_legend","camellia_hill","hydrangea_tunnel","osulloc_tea","amorepacific","innisfree_jeju_house","compound_stop_pattern"],"best_for":["first_time_jeju_visitors","couples","honeymooners","wedding_photo_seekers","instagram_travelers","photographers","botanical_enthusiasts","tea_enthusiasts","families_with_young_kids","seniors_with_moderate_mobility","june_visitors_seeking_hydrangea_tunnel","guests_wanting_garden_plus_geology_combo"],"not_recommended_for":["thrill_seekers","private_tour_seekers","guests_demanding_east_coast_or_unesco_climb_coverage","guests_wanting_seongsan_ilchulbong_or_seongeup_heritage","winter_visitors_seeking_floral_peak","guests_with_severe_pollen_allergies"],"differentiation_vs_east_hydrangea_sister":"Same ''hydrangea festival'' product family, but **southwest garden-plus-geology emphasis**: 3 garden anchors (Hallim + Camellia Hill + Osulloc tea-fields) + 1 compound geology stop (Jusangjeolli+Cheonjeyeon) + 1 west-coast beach (Hyeopjae). The east sister covers **Hamdeok beach + Seongeup Joseon heritage + triple-UNESCO Seongsan + Ilchul Land + Hueree** — a more UNESCO-and-heritage-coded, higher-climb route. Booking matrix: guests with strong wedding-photo or hydrangea-tunnel interest + lower mobility tolerance + multi-garden preference should book southwest; guests with strong UNESCO + Joseon heritage interest + willing to climb Seongsan should book east. **Both routes share Camellia Hill peak alignment in mid-June**, so the operator can offer parallel departures for both routes simultaneously during peak hydrangea weeks.","seasonal_window":{"best_months":["June (peak hydrangea)","May (early hydrangea + Camellia Hill greenhouse)","April (Camellia Hill spring start)","October"],"good_months":["March","September","November (Camellia Hill camellia start)"],"low_season_months":["December","January","February"],"snow_closure_risk":"None — west-coast route is snow-resilient","typhoon_window":"August — typhoon-track season; tour reschedule policy applies"},"kb_anchor_version":"1.21"},"pickup_dropoff":{"type":"hotel_pickup","meeting_points":[{"name":"Hotel within Jeju City","time":"≈08:30 (free)"},{"name":"Hotel outside Jeju City (Seogwipo/Aewol/Seongsan)","time":"Earlier pickup; +₩70,000 surcharge"},{"name":"Jeju International Airport","time":"≈08:30"}],"dropoff_points":[{"name":"Hotel in Jeju City","approx_time":"≈18:00"},{"name":"Dongmun Traditional Market","approx_time":"≈18:00"},{"name":"Jeju Airport","approx_time":"≈18:00"}],"hotel_pickup_available":true,"notes":"Free pickup in Jeju City. Outside-city pickup adds ₩70,000. Hydrangea stops only in bloom late May to mid-July (peak mid-June); check before booking."},"itinerary_variants":[],"priceSource":{"discountPct":10,"discountNote":"10% off marketplace baseline","amount":null,"currency":"USD"},"_publication":{"schema_version":"v4_canonical","last_modified":"2026-04-28","version_history":["v11","v12","v13","v14","v15"],"fix_passes":{"v12":"P0+P1 — pickup_dropoff Schema A unification, routeFlowStops type-based, competing_products → internal slugs, anchor_poi_keys aligned","v13":"P1.5 — pickup_dropoff Schema A.2 → A.1; practicalAccordionItems / routePhases / seasonalVariations unified to V4 canonical (no Tailwind in data)","v14":"P2 — _publication uniform; duration formatting standardized; glanceItems Duration added where missing","v15":"P3 round 1 — SEO trim. seo.pageTitle rewritten to ≤65 chars (was 14/25 over 70); seo.metaDescription rewritten to ≤168 chars (was 25/25 over 170). primaryKeywords and ogImage unchanged. Hero/OG images, POI verification, review imports, and routePhases enrichment deferred to later P3 rounds.","v17_schema_unification":{"date":"2026-04-28","description":"Phase 1: Converted matching_profile scores from 1-5 int scale to 0-1 float scale to match the 3 Step 3 new tours. Mapping 1→0.20, 2→0.40, 3→0.60, 4→0.80, 5→1.00. Mechanical conversion preserves ordinal information; verified-fact recalibration happens in subsequent enhancement batches.","fields_converted":43,"fields_skipped":0,"fields_already_float":0},"v17_batch5_enhancement":{"date":"2026-04-29","description":"Batch 5 deep enhancement — descriptions raised to 700-1300+ chars; KB-backed metadata on all attraction stops; matching_profile recalibrated with verified-fact 0-1 float scores. Time-weighted indoor_ratio per Fix 1 methodology.","_score_audit":{"_methodology":"0-1 float scale. Indoor ratio computed time-weighted with Fix 1 methodology.","deltas_applied":{"unesco_fit":{"old":1,"new":0.45,"reasoning":"Verified — NO direct UNESCO World Heritage stops on this tour. Hallim Park caves are Korean National Monument (No. 236), NOT UNESCO. Jusangjeolli is Korean Natural Monument (No. 443), NOT UNESCO. Cheonjeyeon, Hyeopjae, Camellia Hill, Osulloc are non-UNESCO. Mechanical 1.0 was overstated. 0.45 reflects strong national-heritage anchors but no direct UNESCO."},"walking_level":{"old":0.4,"new":0.5,"reasoning":"Verified: Hyeopjae photo-stop (minimal), Hallim 1.5-3 km flat with cave ducking, Jusangjeolli 0.5 km boardwalk, Cheonjeyeon ~150 stairs to mid falls, Camellia Hill ~1.5 km flat, Osulloc 0.5 km. Total ~5 km mostly flat with one stair section. 0.50 calibrated."},"scenic_level":{"old":1,"new":0.9,"reasoning":"Verified: turquoise beach + 9-area botanical garden + 2 lava-tube caves + columnar basalt cliff + three-tier waterfall + camellia hydrangea tunnel + green tea fields. 7 distinct landscapes — among catalog''s most diverse. 0.90 calibrated."},"photo_level":{"old":1,"new":0.95,"reasoning":"Verified: 6+ hero shots — Hyeopjae beach + Hallim caves/folk village + Jusangjeolli columns + Cheonjeyeon nymphs + Camellia hydrangea tunnel + Osulloc fields. Catalog-leading photo density. 0.95."},"iconic_landmark_fit":{"old":0.8,"new":0.85,"reasoning":"Verified: Hyeopjae Top 3 Jeju beach + Hallim Park 1.2M annual visitors + Jusangjeolli Natural Monument 443 + Cheonjeyeon (only 3-tier falls on Jeju) + Osulloc (Jeju''s most famous tea brand). 5/6 internationally iconic. 0.85."},"indoor_ratio":{"old":0.4,"new":0.2,"reasoning":"CORRECTION using time-weighted method (Fix 1 methodology): 108 indoor / 405 total = 0.27 with lunch; 60/345 = 0.17 without. Catalog value 0.20 represents both. Mechanical 0.4 overstated."},"weather_sensitivity":{"old":1,"new":0.85,"reasoning":"VERIFIED 0.85 — hydrangea bloom timing weather-dependent; Hyeopjae + Jusangjeolli + Camellia Hill + Osulloc all primarily outdoor. Hallim caves provide partial weather refuge."},"rain_fit":{"old":0.6,"new":0.55,"reasoning":"Hallim caves (~600m total) + Osulloc indoor museum + restaurant lunch provide refuge. But majority of stops outdoor. 0.55 calibrated."},"first_time_fit":{"old":1,"new":0.85,"reasoning":"Verified: covers 7 distinct Jeju landscapes — among the most representative single-day southwest summaries. Season-specific to summer for hydrangea. 0.85."},"value_for_money_fit":{"old":0.6,"new":0.7,"reasoning":"Verified fees: Hyeopjae free + Hallim ₩11,000 + Jusangjeolli ₩2,000 + Cheonjeyeon ₩2,500 + Camellia Hill ₩9,000 + Osulloc free = ~₩24,500/adult. Higher than other Jeju tours due to multiple paid stops. 0.70."},"young_kids_fit":{"old":0.8,"new":0.85,"reasoning":"UPGRADED — Hallim Safari Bird Garden + caves + folk village + Hyeopjae Beach + Cheonjeyeon ravine. Strong family appeal. 0.85."},"senior_fit":{"old":0.6,"new":0.65,"reasoning":"UPGRADED — most stops senior-accessible (Hallim flat + Hyeopjae photo-stop + Osulloc flat); Cheonjeyeon stairs are the one challenge. 0.65."},"stroller_fit":{"old":0.6,"new":0.65,"reasoning":"UPGRADED — Hallim caves require ducking; otherwise mostly stroller-friendly. 0.65 calibrated for the cave caveat."},"beach_fit":{"old":0.4,"new":0.55,"reasoning":"UPGRADED — Hyeopjae IS the beach component (Top 3 Jeju). Photo-stop format limits beach time. 0.55."},"culture_level":{"old":0.6,"new":0.55,"reasoning":"Verified: Hallim Folk Village + Cheonjeyeon Seven Nymphs legend + Osulloc tea heritage. 3/6 cultural anchors. 0.55."},"nature_fit":{"old":1,"new":0.9,"reasoning":"Verified: beach + botanical garden + caves + columnar cliff + waterfall + flower park + tea fields. Catalog-leading nature density. 0.90."},"geological_fit":{"old":0.8,"new":0.85,"reasoning":"Verified: Hyeopjaegul + Ssangyonggul caves (lava+limestone) + Jusangjeolli columnar joints. 2 distinct geological landmarks. 0.85."}}},"stops_enhanced":6,"sources":["VisitKorea","Visit Jeju","Hallim Park CVB","AllTrails","Hunting for Bliss","Soul of Seoul","Roaming Sonaa","Trazy","KKday","NOL World"],"_extended_dimensions_documented_only":{"note":"These dimensions (snow_fit, active_fit, geological_fit, experiential_fit) were assessed during the v17 verified-fact audit but are NOT yet part of the standard 68-key matching_profile. They are preserved here as documentation for future schema extension.","values":{"geological_fit":0.85}}}}}}'::jsonb
